29/10/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The justice ministers of several countries in Southeast Europe adopted a declaration Tuesday (28 October) on joint action against organised crime.
The ministers signed the document during the second day of a regional conference held under the South East European Co-operation Process of the Stability Pact.
The countries pledged to provide technical and legal assistance to line institutions.
(HINA, FENA, BBC - 28/10/03)
